node.text:
...sometimes we just need to get out of our own way. 😉 We were designed to self-heal. Our bodies are constantly renewing and rebalancing itself. It is always in communication with us, telling us what it needs. All we need to do is listen.

👉 You're not going to find the answer to long-lasting health from a one-size-fits-all diet or lifestyle change. Health is something that goes beyond the physical. True health is honoring the connection of mind, body, and spirit.

That's why we look to Ayurveda (pronounced "eye-your-vay-duh"), a 5,000-year-old healing system that teaches us a personalized approach to well-being based on our unique mind-body type.

There are many ways to explore the healing wisdom of Ayurveda. We have plenty of free articles on chopra.com. And if you're ready for an interactive, in-person experience, you can join us for our Chopra Health Retreat, hosted twice monthly in Carefree, Arizona. 💛

Our retreat provides customized lifestyle and health recommendations based on your specific needs. Through daily personalized massages, guided meditation and yoga, a 1:1 consultation with an Ayurvedic physician, educational sessions and workshops, and a multi-step detoxification process to aid in the release of toxins, you’ll learn how to take a life-changing, well-rounded approach to your well-being. Is your body saying yes please? 😌 Find a date that works for you via link in bio.

node.text:
A regular daily practice of controlled breathing is one of the best tools for vitality and longevity. 💛 The basis for breathwork originates in the science of yoga, specifically the fourth limb of yoga, known as pranayama, pronounced prah-nah-yam-ah or prah-nah-yam (both can be used).⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Although there are various definitions of the term, one interpretation is: *prana* (life force) and *ayama* (expansion), or expanding the life force using the breath. The ancient yogis learned that by controlling the breath, you can influence every aspect of your life.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Benefits of regular breathwork: ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
✔️ Reduced anxiety and depression⁠⁠
✔️ Lower/stabilized blood pressure⁠⁠
✔️ Increased energy levels⁠⁠
✔️ Improved immunity⁠⁠
✔️ Decreased feelings of stress and overwhelm⁠⁠
✔️ Reduction in PTSD symptoms⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Ready to develop your own pranayama ritual? Join @eddiestern in the Chopra App for his new series, "Breathwork for Balance " – link in bio.

node.text:
In other words...keep on truckin'. 💛  There is no textbook way to experience growth. It looks different and happens at different times for different people. That's what makes us unique. 👉 That said, if you're ready to get unstuck, here are a few tools depending on what you're feeling:⁠
⁠
🙃  In a creative funk? A few minutes of quiet, controlled breathing or a walking meditation can help bring your mind into the present and open the way for new thoughts and ideas. ⁠
⁠
🙃  Stuck on a negative self-belief? Turn around the experiences that made your belief stick. Ask yourself: Who told me this? Was it repeated a lot? Why do I trust the person who told me this? Does holding this belief serve my highest good? Is there a reason to believe the opposite?⁠
⁠
🙃  Stuck in the past? Instead of trying to bury a bad memory, focus on the feeling it carries. The stories of our past don't need to be erased to discharge the emotional debt. Feel it to free it. ⁠
⁠
Inspire the community: What are some of your go-to ways to get unstuck?
